<p>Instead of passing a <code>--env=prod</code> flag to change the environment, this reads
the <code>.env</code> file like normal. Let's try it!</p>
<p>If you're on UNIX, make this executable with a <code>chmod +x</code>. Then run <code>./console</code> or
in Windows <code>php console</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">chmod +x console</div><div class="line">./console</div></code></pre>
<p>That blows up with "Environment file .env not found". I forgot to update my <code>DotEnv</code>
path since this file lives in the root. Make sure you pass it just <code>__DIR__</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="b03295d65b">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
