<p>Try it now:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./console</div></code></pre>
<p>Our mini-app has a fully-fledged console. Instead of <code>./app/console</code>, the command
is just <code>./console</code>, but everything else is the same. Use <code>debug:router</code> to get all
the routes:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./console debug:router</div></code></pre>
<p>And <code>debug:container</code> to see the services:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./console debug:container</div></code></pre>
<p>And the one we want is <code>./console assets:install</code> with a <code>--symlink</code> if your system
supports that.</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./console assets:install --symlink</div></code></pre>
<p>Refresh the 404 page: there's the beautiful exception page we expect.</p>

    
